<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Frappuccino</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/coffeecorner" href="/public/images/logo.png" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css">
  <link href='https://unpkg.com/boxicons@2.1.4/css/boxicons.min.css' rel='stylesheet'>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH" crossorigin="anonymous">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/css/general.css">
</head>
<body>
  <!--Thanh dieu huong-->
  <div id="navbar"></div>

  <!--san pham-->
  <!--hinh giao dien-->
  <section class="hero-section text-center py-5" style="background-image: url(/public/images/frappuccino.png);">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="display-4 text-white">Frappuccino</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <main>
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-6">
          <div>
            <h2>Description</h2>
            <p>
              A Frappuccino is a creamy, sweet, and chilled coffee-based beverage made popular by Starbucks. It combines coffee, milk, sweeteners, and ice, blended to a smooth, frosty consistency
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-6">
          <dl>
            <div class="container-fluid">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12 col-sm-6">
                  <dt>
                    <span>Ingredients</span>
                  </dt>
                  <dd>
                    <ol>
                      <li>
                        Brewed coffee (chilled) or 1-2 shots of espresso: 1/2 cup
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Milk (dairy or non-dairy): 1/2 cup
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Sugar or sweetener: 1-2 tablespoons (to taste)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Ice cubes: 1 to 1.5 cups
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Vanilla extract: 1/4 teaspoon (optional, for flavor)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Whipped cream: For topping (optional)
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Syrup (chocolate, caramel, or any flavor): Optional, for sweetness and drizzle
                      </li>
                    </ol>
                  </dd>
                </div>
                <div class="col-12 col-sm-6">
                  <dt>
                    <span>Equipments</span>
                  </dt>
                  <dd>
                    <ol>
                      <li>
                        Blender
                      </li>
                      <li>
                        Tall glass or mug
                      </li>
                    </ol>
                  </dd>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>1. Prepare the Coffee</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          Brew strong coffee or espresso and let it cool completely. Using chilled coffee prevents the ice from melting too quickly during blending.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>2. Blend Ingredients</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          In a blender, combine chilled coffee, milk, sugar, and ice cubes.
        </li>
        <li>
          Add any optional flavorings like vanilla extract or syrups.
        </li>
        <li>
          Blend on high until smooth and frothy.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>3. Adjust Consistency</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          If the drink is too thick, add a splash of milk or coffee and blend again.
        </li>
        <li>
          If it's too thin, add a few more ice cubes and blend.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
    <section class="py-3">
      <h3>4. Serve</h3>
      <ul class="m-0">
        <li>
          Pour the Frappuccino into a tall glass.
        </li>
        <li>
          Top with whipped cream and drizzle with syrup if desired.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    
  </main>

  <!--footer-->
  <div id="footer"></div>

  <script src="https://unpkg.com/boxicons@2.1.4/dist/boxicons.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js" integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <script>
    fetch('/view/partials/header.html')
      .then(response => response.text())
      .then(data => {
        document.getElementById('navbar').innerHTML = data;
      })
      .catch(error => console.error('Error loading navbar:', error));
  </script>
  <script>
    fetch('/view/partials/footer.html')
      .then(response => response.text())
      .then(data => {
        document.getElementById('footer').innerHTML = data;
      })
      .catch(error => console.error('Error loading navbar:', error));
  </script>
</body>
</html>